,"about 1517":"omkring 1517","1521":"1521","1576":"1576","1565":"1565","1475":"1475","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","1559":"1559","Wales, Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England":"Laughton en le Morthen, Jórvík, England","Wales, Yorkshire, England":"Wales, Jórvík, England","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, England"},"nl":{"1475–3 October 1559":"1475–3 oktober 1559","1484–1524":"1484–1524","1475–Female":"1475–Overleden","1501–1567":"1501–1567","1517–1565":"1517–1565","1521–1576":"1521–1576","1475–1559":"1475–1559","3 October 1559":"3 oktober 1559","1484":"1484","1558":"1558","1524":"1524","1501":"1501","1567":"1567","about 1517":"circa 1517","1521":"1521","1576":"1576","1565":"1565","1475":"1475","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","1559":"1559","Wales, Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England":"Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England","Wales, Yorkshire, England":"Wales, Yorkshire, England","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, England"},"en":{"1475–3 October 1559":"1475–3 October 1559","1484–1524":"1484–1524","1475–Female":"1475–Deceased","1501–1567":"1501–1567","1517–1565":"1517–1565","1521–1576":"1521–1576","1475–1559":"1475–1559","3 October 1559":"3 October 1559","1484":"1484","1558":"1558","1524":"1524","1501":"1501","1567":"1567","about 1517":"about 1517","1521":"1521","1576":"1576","1565":"1565","1475":"1475","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","1559":"1559","Wales, Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England":"Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England","Wales, Yorkshire, England":"Wales, Yorkshire, England","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hewitt","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English:","from the Middle English personal name <i>Hewet</i>, <i>Huet</i>, <i>Hughet</i>, <i>Howet</i>, pet forms of <i>Hugh</i> (Middle English <i>Hewe</i>, <i>Hue</i>; see   Hugh   and compare   Hew  ). The spelling <i>Hughet</i> stood for both <i>Huet</i> and the synonymous <i>Huget</i>; see   Huggett  . This surname has also been established in Ireland since the 14th century.","habitational name from Hewitts in Chelsfield or Hewitts in Willesborough (both Kent), both named from Old English <i>hīewett</i> ‘cutting’, denoting a place where trees had been cut down. Here there lived families called <i>de la Hewatte</i> (1270), <i>de la hewett</i> (1301), and <i>atte Hewete</i> (1338). The name may also be topographic for someone who lived in a newly made clearing in a wood."],"variants":[{"name":"Howatt","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Hewitt  ."]},{"name":"Hewatt","meanings":["English: variant of   Hewitt  ."]},{"name":"Hewitson","meanings":["English (northern): patronymic from the personal name <i>Hewet</i>; see   Hewitt  ."]},{"name":"Howett","meanings":["English (East Midlands): variant of   Hewitt  ."]},{"name":"Huett","meanings":["English (Somerset): variant of   Hewitt  .","German (<b>Hütt</b>): status name for someone living in a hut or owning a small shop, Middle High German <i>hütte</i>, or a habitational name from any of several places called Hütt or Hütte. Compare   Hutt  ."]},{"name":"Hewett","meanings":["English: variant of   Hewitt  ."]},{"name":"Howat","meanings":["Scottish (southwestern): variant of   Hewitt  ."]},{"name":"Howitt","meanings":["English (East Midlands): variant of   Hewitt  ."]},{"name":"Hugh","meanings":["English, Welsh, and Scottish (of Norman origin): from the Old French personal name <i>Hue</i>, from ancient Germanic <i>Hugo</i> (ultimately derived from <i>hugi-</i> ‘mind, spirit’). This was a very popular name in England after the Norman Conquest, partly due to the reputation of Saint Hugh of Lincoln (1140–1200), who was born in Burgundy and who established the first Carthusian monastery in England.","Scottish and Irish: adopted as an Anglicized form of the Gaelic personal name <i>Aodh</i>, a derivative of a Gaelic word meaning ‘fire’. See   Hughes  .","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surnames 邱 and 丘, based on their Hakka pronunciation; see   Qiu   1 and 2."]},{"name":"Huet","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Marcel, Andre.","English: variant of   Hewitt  .","French: from a pet form of the personal name   Hue   ‘Hugh’."]}]},{"name":"Edmund","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From an Old English personal name derived from <i>ēad</i> ‘prosperity, riches’ + <i>mund</i> ‘protector’. It was borne by several early royal and saintly figures, including a 9th-century king of East Anglia killed by invading Danes, allegedly for his adherence to Christianity. In the 16th and 17th centuries, there was a good deal of interchange between <i>Edmund</i> and <i>Edward</i>."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705201,"age":74,"year":"1549","julianDay":2286821,"title":"Book of Common Prayer","description":"Book of Common Prayer, a product of the English Reformation, was published in 1549 for assistance in the administration of the sacraments and other rites and ceremonies of the church according to the use of the Church of England. The book outlined morning, evening, and communion prayers and orders for baptism and marriage, thus making England a truly Protestant state.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Book_of_Common_Prayer","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Book of Common Prayer","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705202,"age":83,"year":"1558","julianDay":2290108,"title":"Act of Uniformity","description":"The Act of Uniformity was passed by the Parliament of England and required all people to go to church once a week. The consequence of not attending church was a fine of 12 pence, which was a considerable amount for a poor person.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Edmund Hewitt was born in 1475, in Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England. He had at least 3 sons with Catherine Essex. He died on 3 October 1559, in Wales, Yorkshire, England, at the age of 84."},"et":{"1475–3 October 1559":"1475–3. oktoober 1559","1484–1524":"1484–1524","1475–Female":"1475–Surnud","1501–1567":"1501–1567","1517–1565":"1517–1565","1521–1576":"1521–1576","1475–1559":"1475–1559","3 October 1559":"3. oktoober 1559","1484":"1484","1558":"1558","1524":"1524","1501":"1501","1567":"1567","about 1517":"umbes 1517","1521":"1521","1576":"1576","1565":"1565","1475":"1475","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","1559":"1559","Wales, Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England":"Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England","Wales, Yorkshire, England":"Wales, Yorkshire, England","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, England"},"fi":{"1475–3 October 1559":"1475–3. lokakuuta 1559","1484–1524":"1484–1524","1475–Female":"1475–Kuollut","1501–1567":"1501–1567","1517–1565":"1517–1565","1521–1576":"1521–1576","1475–1559":"1475–1559","3 October 1559":"3. lokakuuta 1559","1484":"1484","1558":"1558","1524":"1524","1501":"1501","1567":"1567","about 1517":"noin 1517","1521":"1521","1576":"1576","1565":"1565","1475":"1475","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","1559":"1559","Wales, Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England":"Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England","Wales, Yorkshire, England":"Wales, Yorkshire, England","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, England"},"fr":{"1475–3 October 1559":"1475–3 octobre 1559","1484–1524":"1484–1524","1475–Female":"1475–Décédée","1501–1567":"1501–1567","1517–1565":"1517–1565","1521–1576":"1521–1576","1475–1559":"1475–1559","3 October 1559":"3 octobre 1559","1484":"1484","1558":"1558","1524":"1524","1501":"1501","1567":"1567","about 1517":"environ 1517","1521":"1521","1576":"1576","1565":"1565","1475":"1475","1517":"1517","1549":"1549","1559":"1559","Wales, Laughton en le Morthen, Yorkshire, England":"Laughton en le Morthen, Everwyck, Angleterre","Wales, Yorkshire, England":"Wales, Everwyck, Angleterre","Great Bromley, Essex, England":"Great Bromley, Essex, Angleterre","life